The paper presents an approach to semi-supervised learning, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The approach is tested on several data sets, including computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which suggests that these sub-categories are also relevant. Additionally, the paper mentions previous work on coupled priors, which is a technique commonly used in statistical learning (cs.SD).
